On October 13, 2010, the President signed several laws into effect. The "Plain Writing Act of 2010" requires Federal agencies to use plain writing in certain government documents issued to the public. The "Veterans' Benefits Act of 2010" makes changes to various veterans' affairs programs and benefits. H.R. 4543 designates a postal facility in San Jose, California as the "Anthony J. Cortese Post Office Building." H.R. 5341 designates a postal facility in Brighton, Michigan as the "Joyce Rogers Post Office Building." H.R. 5390 designates a postal facility in Cleveland, Ohio as the "David John Donafee Post Office Building." H.R. 5450 designates a postal facility in Los Angeles, California as the "Tom Bradley Post Office Building." Lastly, the "WIPA and PABSS Extension Act of 2010" reauthorizes Social Security Administration work incentive and support programs through FY 2011 to assist certain beneficiaries, including those with disabilities, in returning to the workforce.